epidemic insularity
Symptoms of saying "if you do X, you lose" when X is in vogue.

I thought it might be [a symptom of senility], but it seems to me that some people have this symptom even in high school.

New, a state of being evasive about X, which many people value positively, because of the fact itself.
　The mentality of "I don't like it because it's popular", not because it doesn't fit my values or my tastes.
　In the end, he is 50-50 with the people he hates in that he is influenced by trends rather than having a firm axis of values of his own.

[reverse]
